                        <p class="text_add position-relative mb-0 text-lg-start mt-4">A basic (alkaline) catalyst and, usually but not necessarily, a molar excess of formaldehyde is used to make resol resins. The following two stages describe a simplified view of the reaction: First, phenol reacts with methylene glycol to form methylol phenol: (Phenolic Novolac & Resol Resins text - Resol Resins)</p>
                        
                        <div class="section_28__img-cont position-relative mt-4 ms-0">
